In a phone call, President Obama and President Xi Jinping of China discussed the need for coordinated efforts in response to North Korea's recent nuclear test. Both leaders expressed their commitment to the denuclearization of the Korean Peninsula and stated that they will not accept North Korea as a nuclear weapon state. They also agreed that North Korea's planned ballistic missile test would violate multiple UN Security Council resolutions and be provocative and destabilizing. They emphasized the importance of a strong and unified international response, including through a UN Security Council Resolution.